sql:
SELECT patient_id, patient_name, age, menopause_status, deg_malig, class
FROM patients
WHERE deg_malig = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Tumor size categories are defined as follows: 5 - 25-29mm, 6 - 30-34mm, 7 - 35-39mm; 
- A quarter of an inch is approximately equal to 6.35mm, and half an inch is approximately equal to 12.7mm; 
- The tumor size range of 25-39mm is utilized to define the metaphorical expression "greater than a quarter of an inch and less than or equal to about half an inch."

sql:
SELECT MAX(p.tumor_size) AS largest_tumor_size
FROM patients p
WHERE p.class = 1 AND p.deg_malig = 2;

external_knowledge:
A breast cancer recurrence study is a research study that focuses on patients who have experienced a recurrence of breast cancer; The study aims to understand the factors that contribute to the recurrence and to develop strategies for prevention and treatment; 
Node caps refer to the presence of a capsule around a tumor, which can affect the spread of cancer; 
Degree of malignancy is a measure of how aggressive a cancer is; 
Menopause status is relevant to breast cancer research because the risk of breast cancer changes after menopause.

- Treatment sequence refers to the order in which a patient receives different treatments; 
- Outcome class refers to the category (0 - no recurrence, 1 - recurrence) a patient falls into after a treatment;
- Cumulative outcome count represents the total number of times a patient experiences a specific outcome over the course of their treatments.
